{"title":"Chris King adds Micro Spline freehub bodies for road hubs","link":"https://bikerumor.com/chris-king-micro-spline-road-hubs/","date":1704296863000,"content":"<p><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/chris-king-microspline-freehub-1.jpg\" alt=\"chris king micro spline freehub body shown on a wheel\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/chris-king-microspline-freehub-1.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/chris-king-microspline-freehub-1-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/chris-king-microspline-freehub-1-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/chris-king-microspline-freehub-1-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/chris-king-microspline-freehub-1-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/chris-king-microspline-freehub-1-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/chris-king-microspline-freehub-1-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></p>\n<p>Been wanting to give your gravel bike a mullet drivetrain with Shimano components? Now you can add Chris King’s R45D hubs into that mix, too.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Chris King’s R45D road hubs now have a Micro Spline freehub body option, available on standalone hubs and complete wheels.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/chris-king-microspline-freehub-2.jpg\"><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/chris-king-microspline-freehub-2.jpg\" alt=\"chris king micro spline freehub body shown with cassette attached\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/chris-king-microspline-freehub-2.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/chris-king-microspline-freehub-2-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/chris-king-microspline-freehub-2-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/chris-king-microspline-freehub-2-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/chris-king-microspline-freehub-2-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/chris-king-microspline-freehub-2-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/chris-king-microspline-freehub-2-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Available in Black or Silver, they’re compatible with all Center Lock R45D versions. They’ll also fit 2nd generation 6-bolt hubs with serial numbers starting with 6910. They fit Shimano’s mountain bike cassettes, which can be mixed with the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/shimano-grx-12-speed-mechanical/\">new 12-speed GRX gravel components</a> to create a wider-range 1x drivetrain on gravel bikes.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/chris-king-microspline-freehub-3-scaled.jpg\"><img width=\"2560\" height=\"1707\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/chris-king-microspline-freehub-3-scaled.jpg\" alt=\"chris king micro spline freehub bodies\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/chris-king-microspline-freehub-3-scaled.jpg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/chris-king-microspline-freehub-3-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/chris-king-microspline-freehub-3-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/chris-king-microspline-freehub-3-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/chris-king-microspline-freehub-3-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/chris-king-microspline-freehub-3-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/chris-king-microspline-freehub-3-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/chris-king-microspline-freehub-3-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Existing Chris King hub owners can retrofit with the complete axle-and-freehub body combo for $250 with stainless steel bearings or $310 with ceramic bearings. 12×142 thru axles only.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://go.skimresources.com?id=66154X1653891&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fchrisking.com%2Fproducts%2Fr45d-micro-spline-conversion-kit%3Fvariant%3D40384133759094\" target=\"_blank\">ChrisKing.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/chris-king-micro-spline-road-hubs/\">Chris King adds Micro Spline freehub bodies for road hubs</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Tyler Benedict","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"c4ee2005b097a71518c62c6dc6e5b7f03125d7f6baf4778e7138c66c39c9a3c8","category":"Cycling"}